## Global Communities in MVP

MVP has **4 priority communities** (all use global merit, quota disabled):

| Community | typeTag | Uses global merit |
|-----------|---------|-------------------|
| МД | marathon-of-good | Yes |
| ОБ | future-vision | Yes |
| Projects | team-projects | Yes |
| Feedback | support | Yes |

### 1. Image of Future (ОБ / Obraz Budushchego)

**Main game community.** Participants publish their "images of future" and compete to promote them.

**Key Settings:**

| Setting | Value | Reason |
|---------|-------|--------|
| `settings.allowWithdraw` | **No** | Merits stay on post forever |
| `permissionRules` (self-vote) | **Enabled** | Can support own ОБ |
| `meritSettings.quotaEnabled` | No | Quota disabled in priority communities |
| `tappalkaSettings.enabled` | No | Only voting in this community |
| `settings.postCost` | 1 merit | Standard |
| `settings.pollCost` | 1 merit | Standard |
| `settings.commentMode` | `all` (weighted) | Standard voting/comments behavior |

**Implementation note:** Bootstrap does not set `allowWithdraw`; schema default is `true`. Set `settings.allowWithdraw = false` on the future-vision community to keep merits on posts. Polls: poll creation and casting are blocked for `future-vision` in current routers; `polls.getByCommunity` returns an empty list for this community.

**OB hub, Future Visions feed, `futureVision*` fields, `getFutureVisions`:** @business-future-vision.mdc.

**Special Feature:** Periodically administration rewards authors of highest-rated posts.

---

### 2. Marathon of Good (МД / Marafon Dobra)

**For reports on actually done good deeds.** Main source of merit earning through voting.

#### UI labels vs code identifiers (МД / «Биржа»)

| Layer | Value |
|-------|--------|
| **Community type (API / DB)** | `typeTag === 'marathon-of-good'` |
| **App route** | `/meriter/communities/{communityId}` — `communityId` is the hub’s string id (no `/meriter/birzha` path) |
| **RU nav (bottom bar)** | Short label «Биржа» — i18n key `common.marathonOfGoodLabel` |
| **RU product copy** | Often «Биржа Социальных Инвестиций» in long text (e.g. help, project publish) — marketing / i18n, **not** a `typeTag` |
| **EN nav (bottom bar)** | Default «Exchange» — same key `common.marathonOfGoodLabel` |
| **Desktop sidebar (expanded)** | Tab text uses **`community.name`** from the API for the marathon-of-good row (can match long Russian title) |

Do not use internal tags or Mongo ids as user-visible titles; do not assume a single fixed string in DB matches every i18n variant. Details: @frontend.mdc (Meriter primary navigation).

**Key Settings:**

| Setting | Value | Reason |
|---------|-------|--------|
| `settings.allowWithdraw` | **Yes** | Main earning method |
| `permissionRules` (self-vote) | No | Standard |
| `meritSettings.quotaEnabled` | **No** | Tappalka handles everything |
| `tappalkaSettings.enabled` | **Yes** | Main emission |
| `settings.investingEnabled` | **Yes** | Investment mechanics enabled in current v1 |
| `settings.investorShareMin/Max` | 1..99 | Contract bounds for investors |
| `settings.postCost` | 1 merit | Standard |
| `settings.pollCost` | 1 merit | Standard |
| `settings.commentMode` | `all` (weighted) | Standard voting/comments behavior |

**Implementation note:** No `rateMultiplier` in the community schema. Investment lifecycle uses `settings.requireTTLForInvestPosts`, `settings.maxTTL`, `settings.inactiveCloseDays`, and `settings.distributeAllByContractOnClose` when investing is enabled (see business-communities for full list).

**Birzha posts (exchange feed):** weighted posts live **in** this МД community (`communityId` = marathon-of-good id). They may be created via **`project.publishToBirzha`** (project `postCost` from project `CommunityWallet`) or **`communities.publishToBirzha`** (eligible sources); both attach `sourceEntityId` / `sourceEntityType` for withdrawal and display. Canonical: @business-content.mdc (Exchange publications), @business-projects.mdc (cooperative project path).

